me of the \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases\" rationale=\"Governmental authority\"\u003e\u003ca rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.niddk.nih.gov/health-information/digestive-diseases/acid-reflux-ger-gerd-adults/symptoms-causes\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003emost common causes\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e include \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/323551\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eobesity\u003c/a\u003e and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/10566\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003esmoking\u003c/a\u003e."}]},{"id":"symptoms","title":"Symptoms","isCollapsable":false,"header":["Symptoms"],"body":[{"tagName":"p","source":"The most frequent symptom of acid reflux or heartburn is a feeling of warmth, heat, or burning in the chest and throat. This is due to the stomach acid flowing back up into the esophagus."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Other symptoms \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases\" rationale=\"Governmental authority\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.niddk.nih.gov/health-information/digestive-diseases/acid-reflux-ger-gerd-adults/symptoms-causes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003einclude\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e:"},{"tagName":"ul","source":"\u003cli\u003ea burning sensation in the middle of the chest\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003ea burning, indigestion-like pain\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003ea foul, acrid taste in the mouth\u003c/li\u003e"},{"tagName":"p","source":"If a person experiences acid reflux symptoms often, they should consult a doctor, who may refer them to a \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/327441\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003egastroenterologist\u003c/a\u003e \u003cstrong\u003e\u003cem\u003e—\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/