icles/153390\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eexercising\u003c/a\u003e regularly\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eeating smaller meals more frequently\u003c/li\u003e"},{"tagName":"p","source":"It is of note, however, that these lifestyle modifications may not work for everyone."}]},{"id":"during-pregnancy","title":"During pregnancy","isCollapsable":false,"header":["During pregnancy"],"body":[{"tagName":"p","source":"According to the \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"Department of Health and Human Services\" rationale=\"Governmental authority\"\u003e\u003ca rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.womenshealth.gov/pregnancy/youre-pregnant-now-what/body-changes-and-discomforts\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eOffice on Women’s Health (OWH)\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e, heartburn and \u003ca class=\"content-link css-185ckoq keywords\" title=\"What to know about indigestion or dyspepsia\" href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/163484.php\"\u003eindigestion\u003c/a\u003e are common in pregnancy due to hormonal changes and the baby pressing against the stomach."},{"tagName":"p","source":"The OWH suggest some diet and lifestyle changes that may help relieve the symptoms. These include:"},{"tagName":"ul","source":"\u003cli\u003eeating five to six small meals throughout the day\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003enot lying down within an hour of eating\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003eavoiding fatty and spicy foods\u003c/li\u003e"}]},{"id":"heartburn-vs-heart-attack","title":"Heartburn vs. heart attack","isCollapsable":false,"header":["Heartburn or heart attack?"],"body":[{"tagName":"p","source":"A \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/151444\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eheart attack\u003c/a\u003e is when the arteries connected to the heart become blocked. Heartburn, on the other hand, occurs when stomach acid travels back up the esophagus."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Some symptoms of heartburn and a heart attack could be similar, such as \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/321650\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003echest pain\u003c/a\u003e. As a result, some people who are having a heart attack do not take action as they think they have heartburn."},{"tagName":"p","source":"If a person experiences heartburn pain alongside \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/319175\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eshortness of breath\u003c/a\u003e or sweating, this could be a heart-related issue."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Other symptoms of a heart attack \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"American Heart Associaiton\" rationale=\"Highly respected national organization\"\u003e\u003ca rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.heart.org/en/health-topics/heart-attack/angina-chest-pain/heartburn-or-heart-attack\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003ecan include\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e:"},{"tagName":"ul","source":"\u003cli\u003ediscomfort in the chest, such as squeezing, fullness, pressure, or pain\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/269511\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003enausea\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/323717\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003elightheadedness\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003epain or discomfort in one or both arms, stomach, neck, jaw, or back\u003c/li\u003e"},{"tagName":"p","source":"If a person has some or all of these symptoms, they should seek emergency medical attention. In the words of the American Heart Association (AHA), “If in doubt, check it out.”"},{"tagName":"p","source":"Knowing how to distinguish a heart attack from heartburn can save lives."},{"tagName":"p","source":"\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/312964\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eLearn more about the differences between heartburn and a heart attack here.\u003c/a\u003e"}]},{"id":"treatment","title":"Treatment","isCollapsable":false,"header":["Treatment"],"body":[{"tagName":"p","source":"A person may alleviate symptoms of heartburn by using drugs \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases\" rationale=\"Governmental authority\"\u003e\u003ca rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.niddk.nih.gov/health-information/digestive-diseases/acid-reflux-ger-gerd-adults/treatment\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003esuch as\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e:"},{"tagName":"ul","source":"\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/antacids\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eantacids\u003c/a\u003e, which are over-the-counter (OTC) medications that help relieve mild heartburn\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/proton-pump-inhibitors\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eproton pump inhibitors (PPIs)\u003c/a\u003e, which reduce the amount of stomach acid\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/h2-blockers\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eH2 blockers\u003c/a\u003e, which are a type of medication that reduces the stomach acid levels and may help heal the esophageal lining\u003c/li\u003e"},{"tagName":"p","source":"It is important to note that PPIs heal the esophageal lining and treat GERD symptoms \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"National Institute of Diabetes and Digestive and Kidney Diseases\" rationale=\"Governmental authority\"\u003e\u003ca rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.niddk.nih.gov/health-information/digestive-diseases/acid-reflux-ger-gerd-adults/treatment\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003emore effectively\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e than H2 blockers."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Additionally, H2 blockers can produce various side effects, such as \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/158634\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003ediarrhea\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/150322\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003econstipation\u003c/a\u003e, \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/322047\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eupset stomach\u003c/a\u003e, and \u003ca href=\"https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/73936\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eheadaches\u003c/a\u003e."},{"tagName":"p","source":"In 2020, the \u003chl-trusted-source source=\"Food and Drug Administration (FDA)\" rationale=\"Governmental authority\"\u003e\u003ca rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" href=\"https://www.fda.gov/news-events/press-announcements/fda-requests-removal-all-ranitidine-products-zantac-market\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"content-link css-185ckoq\"\u003eFood and Drug Administration (FDA)\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/hl-trusted-source\u003e requested that manufacturers remove all forms of prescription and OTC ranitidine (Zantac), an H2 blocker, from the market because of its unacceptable levels of N-Nitrosodimethylamine, a probable carcinogen."}]},{"id":"prevention","title":"Prevention","isCollapsable":false,"header":["Prevention"],"body":[{"tagName":"p","source":"Changes to lifestyle and behavior can prevent or improve heartburn symptoms."},{"tagName":"p","source":"A person may prevent heartburn by avoiding acidic foods and drinks that contain caffeine."},{"tagName":"p","source":"Getting more exercise, reaching or maintaining a moderate weight, eating smaller meals, and sitting upright after eating may also help avert heartburn."}]},{"id":"summary","title":"Summary","isCollapsable":false,"header":["Summary"],"body":[{"tagName":"p","source":"Many people experience heartburn occasionally. Usually, it is no cause for concern."},{"tagName":"p","source":"However, if a person has heartburn regularly, they should contact a healthcare professional, who may recommend dietary changes and regular exercise and make suggestions with regard to posture, among other things."},{"tagName":"p","source":"If lifestyle and behavioral changes do not prove effective, a doctor may recommend OTC medications, such as antacids or H2 blockers."},{"tagName":"p","source":"If a person is unsure whether they are experiencing symptoms of heartburn or a heart attack, they should seek immediate medical attention. "}]}],"hasAffiliateLinks":false,"affiliates":[],"propsFor":{"articleResources":[{"displayLink":"gi.org/topics/acid-reflux/","link":"https://gi.org/topics/acid-reflux/","title":{"tagName":"span","source":"Acid reflux. (n.d.)."}},{"displayLink":"niddk.nih.gov/health-information/digestive-diseases/acid-reflux-ger-gerd-adults","link":"https://www.niddk.nih.gov/health-information/digestive-diseases/acid-reflux-ger-gerd-adults","title":{"tagName":"span","source":"Acid reflux (GER \u0026amp; GERD) in adults. (n.d.)."}},{"displayLink":"fda.gov/news-events/press-announcements/fda-requests-removal-all-ranitidine-products-zantac-market","link":"https://www.fda.gov/news-events/press-announcements/fda-requests-removal-all-ranitidine-products-zantac-market","title":{"tagName":"span","source":"FDA requests removal of all ranitidine products (Zantac) from the market [Press release]. (2020)."}},{"displayLink":"heart.org/en/health-topics/heart-attack","link":"https://www.heart.org/en/health-topics/heart-attack","title":{"tagName":"span","source":"Heart attack. (n.d.)."}},{"displayLink":"ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK279254/","link":"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK279254/","title":{"tagName":"span","source":"Heartburn and GERD: Overview. (2018)."}},{"displayLink":"womenshealth.gov/pregnancy","link":"https://www.womenshealth.gov/pregnancy","title":{"tagName":"span","source":"Pregnancy. (2018)."}}],"byline":{"authors":[{"id":1246,"name":{"display":"Markus MacGill","first":"Markus","last":"MacGill"},"lin